Package com.terturl.MMO.MMOEntity

package com.terturl.MMO.MMOEntity
  • Class Summary
    Class
    Description
    BlockBenchFile
    A BlockBenchFile is just a Java representation of the information gathered from a .bbmodel file imported in to use files object placements and rotations to be used in game
    MMOMob
    A finished product of the actual Mob the player will see in game.
    MMOMobEntity
    A base class that represents all locations and positions of BBOBones and animations that will be used for the creation of a MMOMob when spawned into the world
    MMOMobManager
    Handles the creation of MMOMobs and tracking of alive MMOMobs
    MobFileReader
    Will create and generate MMOMobEntity files and call the ResourcePackGenerator to start generating the resource pack to visually see the mob in Spigot
